WEBVTT

00:08.176 --> 00:11.079
[electronic music]

00:11.179 --> 00:15.383
- * MTV

00:34.835 --> 00:36.003
[VCR clicks]

00:36.104 --> 00:39.006
[soft music]

00:39.107 --> 00:42.976
*

00:43.077 --> 00:46.147
- We shouldn't concentrate too
much on superstar, you know?

00:46.247 --> 00:48.349
*

00:48.449 --> 00:50.418
It's a very dangerous thing
to talk about.

00:50.518 --> 00:52.520
*

00:52.620 --> 00:54.755
I know--I know a lot
of superstars...

00:54.855 --> 00:56.890
- Yeah.
- And I look back

00:56.990 --> 00:59.127
and I see--I don't see them
now, you know?

00:59.227 --> 01:00.928
So the same could
happen with us.

01:03.597 --> 01:05.833
* Girl, you know it,
girl, you know it *

01:05.933 --> 01:08.035
* Girl, you know it's true

01:08.136 --> 01:10.704
[dramatic music]

01:13.006 --> 01:15.676
[cheers and applause]

01:15.776 --> 01:18.179
- Milli Vanilli,
the striking European duo,

01:18.279 --> 01:20.581
has made it big in America.

01:20.681 --> 01:23.717
- First album went six times
platinum in 1989.

01:23.817 --> 01:25.753
- It's quite a weird story.

01:25.853 --> 01:27.221
One minute,
Milli Vanilli were there...

01:27.321 --> 01:28.556
- Milli Vanilli.
- Milli Vanilli.

01:28.656 --> 01:29.590
- Milli--
- Milli--

01:29.690 --> 01:31.659
- Milli--
- Vanilli!

01:31.759 --> 01:33.127
- And the next minute,
they weren't.

01:33.227 --> 01:34.295
- [laughs]

01:34.395 --> 01:38.632
*

01:38.732 --> 01:41.068
- New weasel boys of
the record world.

01:41.169 --> 01:44.872
- Everybody participated,
but they were the scapegoats.

01:44.972 --> 01:48.442
- Record companies are oddly
silent on the whole issue.

01:48.542 --> 01:50.811
- People don't understand

01:50.911 --> 01:53.847
the machine that is
underneath a pop act.

01:53.947 --> 01:56.950
- We want to say thank you
to our producer.

01:57.050 --> 01:58.852
- The evil genius,
I guess we could call him.

01:58.952 --> 02:01.355
- If it wasn't for him,
this would not even take place.

02:01.455 --> 02:02.756
- You get something,

02:02.856 --> 02:04.792
but for that, you make
a pact with the devil.

02:04.892 --> 02:09.263
*

02:09.363 --> 02:10.298
- Imagine you have
everything...

02:10.398 --> 02:12.400
[crowd screaming]

02:12.500 --> 02:15.068
- The fame, the fortune.

02:15.169 --> 02:16.837
They were in a dream.

02:16.937 --> 02:18.806
- And suddenly,
everybody turns against you

02:18.906 --> 02:20.674
and you have nothing.
Overnight.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.142
[indistinct shouting]

02:22.243 --> 02:24.312
How do you handle that?

02:24.412 --> 02:26.614
- It cost them everything.

02:26.714 --> 02:29.149
- There is not another story
like this

02:29.250 --> 02:30.818
in pop music history.

02:30.918 --> 02:37.891
*

03:32.780 --> 03:34.748
- It's been a while.

03:34.848 --> 03:36.884
Oh!

03:37.651 --> 03:40.888
Yeah, man, we were
young and fresh, man.

03:40.988 --> 03:45.626
That's a normal tank top but
I think he just pulled on it.

03:45.726 --> 03:48.562
You know, I mean,
we were fashion forward.

03:48.662 --> 03:51.965
[laughs]

03:53.967 --> 03:56.604
That was a big show in Germany.

03:56.704 --> 03:58.906
Yeah, that was a cool vibe.

04:02.410 --> 04:03.877
Hmm.

04:05.212 --> 04:08.349
You know, Rob Pilatus doesn't
look right in this photo.

04:08.449 --> 04:11.519
I can see the decline.

04:11.619 --> 04:15.222
'Cause that's not
what Rob looked like

04:15.323 --> 04:17.725
or was supposed to look like.

04:17.825 --> 04:20.661
He was extremely strong,

04:20.761 --> 04:26.667
but you can tell that
life took a toll on him.

04:29.337 --> 04:32.239
[soft music]

04:32.340 --> 04:35.008
*

04:35.108 --> 04:39.146
Becoming friends
was inevitable.

04:39.246 --> 04:41.882
*

04:41.982 --> 04:43.651
I grew up in Paris.

04:43.751 --> 04:45.719
*

04:45.819 --> 04:52.526
When I turned 18,
I went to Munich, Germany,

04:52.626 --> 04:54.595
ran out of money,

04:54.695 --> 04:59.933
ended up being homeless for
a couple weeks.

05:00.033 --> 05:03.837
It was cold so I had to
sleep in the train station,

05:03.937 --> 05:06.474
but I was able to
get some jobs

05:06.574 --> 05:09.343
teaching classes
with dance school,

05:09.443 --> 05:11.679
'cause that was my background
in Paris.

05:13.146 --> 05:16.750
And then one day,
I went to a party in Munich

05:16.850 --> 05:19.319
and there he was,
Mr. Rob Pilatus.

05:19.420 --> 05:21.188
[hip-hop music]

05:21.288 --> 05:22.723
He was a break-dancer.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.992
He was onstage
doing the helicopter.

05:25.092 --> 05:29.029
*

05:29.129 --> 05:30.330
At the end,

05:30.431 --> 05:32.400
when everybody gave him
his props and everything,

05:32.500 --> 05:34.067
he saw me and he was like,

05:34.167 --> 05:36.737
"Who the hell are you?
That's my turf!"

05:36.837 --> 05:38.338
Because there were not
many Black people

05:38.439 --> 05:39.673
in Munich at the time.

05:39.773 --> 05:41.942
[soft hip-hop music]

05:42.042 --> 05:44.578
Rob and I were the only
dark-skinned people.

05:44.678 --> 05:47.014
There were none.

05:47.114 --> 05:49.983
Rob was older than me
by two years.

05:50.083 --> 05:51.485
He had an infectious laugh--

05:51.585 --> 05:52.820
[imitating laugh]

05:52.920 --> 05:55.489
Like, really loud, you know?

05:55.589 --> 05:56.990
I was socially awkward.

05:57.090 --> 06:01.061
You know, I was shy and
I was not fluent in German.

06:01.161 --> 06:03.631
It was like big brother,
little brother.

06:03.731 --> 06:05.566
*

06:05.666 --> 06:08.268
He became my best friend.

06:08.368 --> 06:10.838
But I felt like there was
something inside of him

06:10.938 --> 06:13.474
that was--that was missing.

06:13.574 --> 06:16.477
[soft music]

07:16.604 --> 07:20.040
- Every time we talked about
that period of his life,

07:20.140 --> 07:22.676
it was kind of like taboo,

07:22.776 --> 07:26.446
but I understood his pain.

07:26.547 --> 07:30.083
Growing up, my family
was so dysfunctional.

07:30.183 --> 07:33.721
It was an abusive environment,

07:33.821 --> 07:37.457
and I ran away.

07:37.558 --> 07:39.793
So, just like me,

07:39.893 --> 07:41.529
he was looking for a family.

07:41.629 --> 07:44.665
[soft determined music]

07:44.765 --> 07:49.469
We moved in together in
an attic of a friend of his.

07:49.570 --> 07:53.574
Rob would take the bed,
I would take the sofa.

07:53.674 --> 07:56.476
But there was, like,
a stereo system,

07:56.577 --> 07:58.345
and that thing was on all day.

07:58.445 --> 08:01.014
[grungy hip-hop music]

08:01.114 --> 08:03.751
Music always
pulled us together.

08:03.851 --> 08:05.485
*

08:05.586 --> 08:07.487
We both liked dancing,

08:07.588 --> 08:10.057
we were very social people,

08:10.157 --> 08:12.425
so we started throwing
parties together.

08:12.526 --> 08:14.027
[upbeat music]

08:14.127 --> 08:15.462
And they were packed.

08:15.563 --> 08:17.364
The girls were beautiful.

08:17.464 --> 08:18.966
You know, we had a DJ,

08:19.066 --> 08:21.301
and we brought the vibe.

08:21.401 --> 08:22.770
*

08:22.870 --> 08:24.772
You know, a circle
would be happening.

08:24.872 --> 08:26.807
Rob doing break dancing,
and when he was done,

08:26.907 --> 08:28.876
I would come in
and I would pop, lock,

08:28.976 --> 08:30.611
bam, bam, bam!

08:30.711 --> 08:33.213
And it brought
a lot of attention.

08:33.313 --> 08:38.185
So we started doing shows
in this club, Piantz.

08:38.285 --> 08:40.654
We loved to entertain
people, like,

08:40.754 --> 08:43.323
make people like, "Aw, yeah!"

08:43.423 --> 08:46.059
We loved that energy,
that roar,

08:46.159 --> 08:48.862
and we wanna do more of this.

08:48.962 --> 08:50.898
And the dream was to do
what we did in the club,

08:50.998 --> 08:54.267
sing, perform, live the life,

08:54.367 --> 08:58.405
to become the biggest pop stars
in the world!

08:58.505 --> 09:00.540
- * Hot girl, hot girl

09:00.641 --> 09:02.175
* I'm satisfaction, baby

09:02.275 --> 09:04.111
* Hot girl, hot girl

09:04.211 --> 09:06.880
- We started dancing
for this TV show.

09:06.980 --> 09:08.281
- * Hot girl

09:08.381 --> 09:12.820
We danced behind pop stars
of the '80s.

09:12.920 --> 09:14.888
We ended up modeling as well.

09:14.988 --> 09:16.423
*

09:16.523 --> 09:18.592
We did some catalog.

09:18.692 --> 09:21.428
We were making a lot of noise
in Munich at that time,

09:21.528 --> 09:24.564
but it was like, how do
we get to the next level?

09:24.665 --> 09:26.366
[upbeat curious music]

09:26.466 --> 09:30.037
In order to become pop stars,
we had to have the look,

09:30.137 --> 09:34.041
so we had to study
what makes a superstar.

09:34.141 --> 09:36.777
And one thing we noticed was
the hair.

09:36.877 --> 09:38.078
*

09:38.178 --> 09:39.780
I know Elvis' hair.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.381
I know Bob Marley's hair.

09:41.481 --> 09:44.217
Marilyn Monroe.
Michael Jackson.

09:44.317 --> 09:47.054
You could put, like, a shadow,
and you knew who that was.

09:47.154 --> 09:49.823
We were like,
"Hell yeah, we're doing this."

09:49.923 --> 09:50.991
And the hair came...

09:51.091 --> 09:54.027
[snaps]
Like that.

09:54.127 --> 09:56.864
Hoo!
The reactions were amazing.

09:56.964 --> 09:58.431
Every time we went to
the clubs,

09:58.531 --> 10:01.468
girls loved the hair,
loved the clothing--

10:01.568 --> 10:02.870
they loved Rob and Fab.

10:02.970 --> 10:05.205
- * Go to the dance floor,
dansez *

10:05.305 --> 10:08.008
* Voulez vous, dansez

10:08.108 --> 10:09.843
- We put a band together,

10:09.943 --> 10:11.945
Empire Bizarre...

10:12.045 --> 10:13.847
- * Hey

10:13.947 --> 10:15.749
- And we played a few gigs.

10:15.849 --> 10:17.617
We gave tapes to people.

10:17.718 --> 10:19.086
We knew we were gonna be big.

10:19.186 --> 10:20.320
- * Dansez

10:43.911 --> 10:45.645
- Since we were
spreading the word

10:45.746 --> 10:47.915
of us getting into
the music industry,

10:48.015 --> 10:50.483
we were starting to
get approached by people.

10:50.583 --> 10:52.185
[soft music]

10:52.285 --> 10:55.588
So one day, this guy came to
Rob and said, "Hey, you know,

10:55.689 --> 10:56.990
we're gonna connect you with
Frank Farian."

10:57.090 --> 10:59.292
*

10:59.392 --> 11:01.862
Rob played cool to the dude,

11:01.962 --> 11:04.231
but to me, he was like,
"Oh, my God!

11:04.331 --> 11:07.267
Oh, Frank Farian!
You know this?" I didn't know.

11:07.367 --> 11:09.069
*

11:09.169 --> 11:11.438
Rob told me,
"Hey, Frank Farian,

11:11.538 --> 11:12.973
he did Boney M."

11:13.073 --> 11:16.076
I was like,
"Oh, wow, that's--that's big"

11:16.176 --> 11:19.146
because Boney M., obviously,
was a huge group.

11:19.246 --> 11:22.049
[Boney M's "Rasputin"
playing]

11:22.149 --> 11:26.720
*

11:26.820 --> 11:30.290
- * There lived a certain man
in Russia long ago *

11:30.390 --> 11:34.762
- * He was big and strong,
in his eyes a flaming glow *

11:34.862 --> 11:38.198
- Boney M. were a big hit
disco group in the '70s...

11:38.298 --> 11:39.499
- Boney M.!
[cheers and applause]

11:39.599 --> 11:42.135
- And they were huge worldwide.
- Huge!

11:42.235 --> 11:45.906
- * He could preach the Bible
like a preacher *

11:46.006 --> 11:47.507
* Full of ecstasy

11:47.607 --> 11:49.276
- Boney M. sold 80 million
records.

11:49.376 --> 11:51.311
They had a number of
number one hits.

11:51.411 --> 11:52.846
- "Rivers of Babylon."

11:52.946 --> 11:54.347
- "Daddy Cool."
- "Sunny."

11:54.447 --> 11:55.682
- I love the song "Ma Baker."

11:55.783 --> 11:57.217
- Ra, ra, Rasputin.

11:57.317 --> 12:00.854
- * Ra, ra, Rasputin,
lover of the Russian queen *

12:00.954 --> 12:03.556
- A bananas song
and it's about Rasputin.

12:03.656 --> 12:06.526
- Mysterious figure
in czarist Russia.

12:06.626 --> 12:08.128
- When you watch video
of Boney M.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.797
and you see Bobby Farrell,
you're like,

12:09.897 --> 12:11.999
"Wow, that dude is awesome."

12:12.099 --> 12:14.067
- It was on the radio,
at parties.

12:14.167 --> 12:16.336
- Boney M. made music that
you could dance to

12:16.436 --> 12:19.472
and get drunk to and have fun.
[laughs]

12:19.572 --> 12:23.243
- But how did you four people
get together to form Boney M.?

12:23.343 --> 12:27.815
- Well, it all came about from
our producer Frank Farian.

12:27.915 --> 12:30.884
[soft tense music]

12:30.984 --> 12:33.620
- If you work with
Frank Farian,

12:33.720 --> 12:36.389
that's a high level guy.

12:36.489 --> 12:40.593
We realized that this could be
the one we've been waiting for,

12:40.693 --> 12:42.462
so we went to Frankfurt.

12:42.562 --> 12:46.199
*

12:46.299 --> 12:50.403
Frank Farian's
compound was huge.

12:50.503 --> 12:52.772
And when they opened the door,

12:52.873 --> 12:57.010
we were greeted by all those
gold records on the wall,

12:57.110 --> 12:59.312
and it was amazing.

12:59.412 --> 13:02.049
It was the kind of stuff that
you saw with Quincy Jones.

13:02.149 --> 13:04.017
*

13:04.117 --> 13:09.256
100 tracks, Neve console,
microphones.

13:09.356 --> 13:12.259
It was incredible!

13:13.560 --> 13:16.329
Frank and his secretary,
Ingrid Segieth,

13:16.429 --> 13:18.498
they said,
"We're working on a project

13:18.598 --> 13:20.667
and we're thinking that
you could be good for it,"

13:20.767 --> 13:22.335
if we were interested.

13:22.435 --> 13:25.538
Hell, yeah, we were interested.

13:25.638 --> 13:29.076
Ingrid brought in
the recording contract,

13:29.176 --> 13:31.979
and we never really
attempted to read it.

13:32.079 --> 13:36.716
We were not trying to say no
to this powerful producer.

13:36.816 --> 13:40.787
Also, we would get, like,
1,500 deutschmark each,

13:40.888 --> 13:45.025
and we were like,
"Oh, hell yeah. Where? OK."

13:45.125 --> 13:48.061
[suspicious music]

13:48.161 --> 13:51.164
When we signed that contract,

13:51.264 --> 13:52.665
we toasted.

13:52.765 --> 13:54.968
*

13:55.068 --> 13:56.836
We were, like, breaking bread.

13:56.937 --> 13:58.872
*

13:58.972 --> 14:02.910
But then Frank leaned over
to Rob and told him,

14:03.010 --> 14:05.845
"Don't fuck with me.

14:05.946 --> 14:07.780
Don't ever fuck with me."

14:07.881 --> 14:10.717
[soft curious music]

14:10.817 --> 14:15.122
*

14:15.222 --> 14:19.559
Several months went by.

14:19.659 --> 14:24.197
They never gave us
any information.

14:24.297 --> 14:25.532
That was driving us crazy.

14:25.632 --> 14:27.467
Like, why don't
they tell us, like,

14:27.567 --> 14:30.938
a date where we can come
to do the vocals,

14:31.038 --> 14:33.974
or like, when do
we get started?

14:34.074 --> 14:37.010
*

14:37.110 --> 14:39.612
Finally, Ingrid called.

14:39.712 --> 14:42.349
"Come to studio.
It's gonna be good."

14:42.449 --> 14:45.352
Oh, man, we were pumped.

14:45.452 --> 14:48.821
We went straight to
the studio.

14:48.922 --> 14:51.858
And then once everyone is
in the room,

14:51.959 --> 14:53.860
he plays a tune.

14:53.961 --> 14:56.063
[machine clicks]

14:56.163 --> 14:58.966
["Girl You Know It's True"
playing]

14:59.066 --> 15:04.237
*

15:04.337 --> 15:08.641
I couldn't believe that
this music was for us.

15:08.741 --> 15:14.081
*

15:14.181 --> 15:15.282
I saw colors.

15:15.382 --> 15:18.151
I saw us onstage

15:18.251 --> 15:20.753
singing in front of a crowd.

15:20.853 --> 15:22.489
And then when
the music stopped...

15:22.589 --> 15:25.192
[music stops]
It was like, wow.

15:25.292 --> 15:27.327
You could still
hear those bells--

15:27.427 --> 15:29.896
ding, ding, ding, ding.

15:32.132 --> 15:35.368
He turned, and then,

15:35.468 --> 15:38.338
you know, "folgen Sie mir."
You know, "follow me."

15:38.438 --> 15:40.807
[soft tense music]

15:40.907 --> 15:42.009
- [speaking German]

15:42.109 --> 15:43.210
- It felt serious.

15:43.310 --> 15:45.512
*

15:45.612 --> 15:48.648
And then we end up
in this dark room.

15:48.748 --> 15:52.319
Rob and Frank start talking
really fast in German,

15:52.419 --> 15:54.787
so I can't really understand
everything,

15:54.887 --> 15:57.457
but I can tell, like,
it's getting intense.

15:57.557 --> 15:59.993
Like, they raise their voices.

16:00.093 --> 16:02.362
Rob is looking at me with
his green eyes.

16:02.462 --> 16:03.930
Like, he looks pissed.

16:04.031 --> 16:05.598
*

16:05.698 --> 16:08.835
Frank leaves and screams,

16:08.935 --> 16:11.604
and then Rob turns to me,
saying,

16:11.704 --> 16:14.307
"They don't want us to sing
on this record."

16:14.407 --> 16:16.309
And I'm like, like--

16:16.409 --> 16:18.245
So, I'm trying to speak.

16:18.345 --> 16:19.379
I'm trying to talk to him

16:19.479 --> 16:20.747
and trying to get
as much information,

16:20.847 --> 16:22.582
but he was like,
"Just wait, wait.

16:22.682 --> 16:24.784
"They don't want us to sing!

16:24.884 --> 16:27.120
They want us to
lip-sync the song."

16:27.220 --> 16:28.588
I'm like, "What?"

16:28.688 --> 16:31.558
Why in the hell?
Like, he's playing us a song.

16:31.658 --> 16:34.227
I'm trying to understand,
like, what do you mean?

16:34.327 --> 16:35.795
I don't get it.

16:35.895 --> 16:37.930
And that's where I--I--
I black out.

16:38.031 --> 16:40.533
[music fades out]

16:40.633 --> 16:42.935
[soft suspicious music]

16:43.036 --> 16:45.138
I remember thinking,
"This is weird.

16:45.238 --> 16:47.740
Like, we don't want to
lip-sync."

16:47.840 --> 16:52.445
That's when Ingrid
gave us the options.

16:54.047 --> 16:58.485
What she conveyed to us
clearly is that

16:58.585 --> 17:02.522
we signed the contract,
we got money--

17:02.622 --> 17:05.892
if we didn't want to
take part,

17:05.992 --> 17:08.261
we have to pay them back.

17:08.361 --> 17:09.929
But Ingrid said,

17:10.029 --> 17:13.032
"It's not just the advance
that we paid you,

17:13.133 --> 17:15.034
"but also all the money that
we gave you

17:15.135 --> 17:17.404
through the months."

17:17.504 --> 17:19.972
We developed a debt
towards Frank Farian.

17:20.073 --> 17:22.309
*

17:22.409 --> 17:24.877
We were scared as hell.

17:24.977 --> 17:28.381
I was 21 years old
and Rob was 24.

17:28.481 --> 17:32.051
*

17:32.152 --> 17:34.587
We had nowhere to go.

17:34.687 --> 17:37.524
So we thought,
OK, it's one song.

17:37.624 --> 17:39.826
You do that and you're out.

17:39.926 --> 17:44.697
[water rushing]

17:44.797 --> 17:47.800
[Boney M's "Sunny" playing]

17:47.900 --> 17:54.874
*

17:56.576 --> 17:59.546
- * Sunny

17:59.646 --> 18:04.384
* Yesterday, my life was
filled with rain *

18:04.484 --> 18:07.053
* Sunny

18:07.154 --> 18:12.125
* You smiled at me and
really eased the pain *

18:12.225 --> 18:13.426
* Sunny

18:13.526 --> 18:20.467
*

18:22.535 --> 18:25.372
- Hold on.
[chuckles]

18:25.472 --> 18:28.775
I should not be so funny.

18:28.875 --> 18:31.043
Serious.

18:31.144 --> 18:34.080
[laughs]

18:34.181 --> 18:36.115
This is serious.

18:36.216 --> 18:38.718
Thank you, schatzi.
[kisses]

18:39.919 --> 18:41.321
- Interview, "Milli."
Take one.

18:41.421 --> 18:43.523
Camera A and B, mark.

18:43.623 --> 18:46.159
- I've heard that
the name Milli Vanilli

18:46.259 --> 18:47.727
is because of you.

18:47.827 --> 18:49.229
- Oh.
- Is that true?

18:49.329 --> 18:50.497
- That's true.

18:50.597 --> 18:52.665
[soft music]

18:52.765 --> 18:54.867
I was Frank's girlfriend.

19:07.514 --> 19:10.983
I wrote the checks because
I was the financial controller

19:11.083 --> 19:13.553
of Frank's company.

19:19.392 --> 19:20.693
When they came into
the studio,

19:20.793 --> 19:22.995
they looked fantastic.

19:23.095 --> 19:26.132
I never saw people like that
so well-dressed

19:26.233 --> 19:27.834
and good-looking and braids,

19:27.934 --> 19:30.503
and Rob's eyes, green--
[gasps]

19:30.603 --> 19:32.305
You couldn't stop
looking at him.

19:32.405 --> 19:34.541
*

19:47.487 --> 19:50.757
But they were
such good dancers.

20:01.568 --> 20:03.770
- Frank needed American singer
like me.

20:03.870 --> 20:05.305
He said,
"I'm gonna make a project

20:05.405 --> 20:07.274
and you'll be the lead singer."

20:07.374 --> 20:08.908
I said, "OK, let's do it."

20:14.314 --> 20:16.383
- I'm from Houston, Texas.

20:16.483 --> 20:18.251
Frank says,
"I have a new project.

20:18.351 --> 20:19.486
Can you rap it?"

20:19.586 --> 20:22.389
He wrote me a check
for $12,000.

20:22.489 --> 20:24.257
Just keep your mouth shut.

20:24.357 --> 20:27.627
- Frank said, "Linda, we're
gonna need backing vocalists."

20:27.727 --> 20:29.262
So I brought in
my twin sister Jodie.

20:29.362 --> 20:31.063
- And I looked at her, I said,
"If this is 'oohs' and 'ahs'

20:31.163 --> 20:33.300
and 'I love you,'
I'm gonna shoot you."

20:33.400 --> 20:34.567
- I said, "Shut up."

20:34.667 --> 20:36.336
He hits it, he says,
"I want you to sing this."

20:36.436 --> 20:37.937
both: * Ooh, ooh, ooh

20:38.037 --> 20:39.105
- * I love you
- I said, "Don't say it!"

20:39.205 --> 20:40.807
[suspicious music]

20:48.247 --> 20:52.319
The song is ready,
and the two guys--perfect.

20:52.419 --> 20:55.555
*

20:55.655 --> 20:57.590
- When they're told
they're gonna lip-sync,

20:57.690 --> 20:59.191
what's their reaction?

20:59.292 --> 21:00.660
- No problem at all.

21:00.760 --> 21:04.631
They agreed and said,
"OK, when can we start?"

21:04.731 --> 21:07.300
It was never an--an--
an argument.

21:07.400 --> 21:09.736
Never ever. Never!

21:09.836 --> 21:13.039
- So you didn't have to
convince them to lip-sync?

21:13.139 --> 21:14.641
- No! Why?

21:14.741 --> 21:17.310
[soft dark music]

21:17.410 --> 21:19.078
They want to have success
and...

21:27.620 --> 21:30.623
- Was there ever
a point you said,

21:30.723 --> 21:33.159
give us the advance back
that we gave you.

21:33.259 --> 21:34.461
- [sigh] Gosh.
No.

21:34.561 --> 21:35.662
- No?
- No.

21:35.762 --> 21:37.697
- You didn't ask--
- No, no, no.

21:37.797 --> 21:42.268
This is not Frank's art--
artwork, yeah.

21:42.369 --> 21:44.904
If they would refuse,
they can go back to Munich

21:45.004 --> 21:46.639
and can...
[flaps lips]

21:46.739 --> 21:48.307
go for...

21:49.409 --> 21:51.043
or something like that.

21:51.143 --> 21:52.645
[chuckles softly]

21:52.745 --> 21:57.750
*

21:57.850 --> 21:59.986
- Well, I, uh...
[clears throat]

22:00.086 --> 22:05.658
The first time I went to share
my side, uh,

22:05.758 --> 22:06.993
I was young.

22:07.093 --> 22:10.262
And if you're a young artist,

22:10.363 --> 22:14.834
you can only tell what
they want you to tell.

22:14.934 --> 22:17.537
But now, fuck it.

22:17.637 --> 22:19.071
[laughs]

22:19.171 --> 22:22.141
I ain't keeping
my mouth shut for nobody.

22:22.241 --> 22:23.876
*

22:23.976 --> 22:28.615
Frank Farian, he was just a--

22:28.715 --> 22:34.220
a genius of his art
of making money.

22:34.320 --> 22:37.924
He knew exactly
what he was doing.

22:38.024 --> 22:40.493
You know,
it's not the first time.

22:40.593 --> 22:43.095
The same game was played with
Boney M.

22:43.195 --> 22:46.566
*

22:46.666 --> 22:50.537
Bobby was not a singer.

22:50.637 --> 22:51.704
He was a dancer.

22:51.804 --> 22:54.607
*

22:54.707 --> 22:56.308
He was a dancer.

23:03.382 --> 23:05.084
- And who sung?

23:05.184 --> 23:05.918
Frank.

23:06.018 --> 23:11.491
- [distorted vocals]

23:11.591 --> 23:14.126
- And it sold

23:14.226 --> 23:16.028
how many platinums,
how many golds,

23:16.128 --> 23:17.396
you know what I'm saying?

23:25.472 --> 23:28.975
- You're looking at him as
a producer

23:29.075 --> 23:32.812
that made most his money
on Black artists,

23:32.912 --> 23:34.847
and it worked.

23:34.947 --> 23:36.649
Then years later, he came back

23:36.749 --> 23:39.786
and did it again
with Milli Vanilli.

23:39.886 --> 23:43.222
*

23:43.322 --> 23:45.525
He took my voice,

23:45.625 --> 23:49.696
he took their faces,

23:49.796 --> 23:52.965
he put the project together,

23:53.065 --> 23:56.368
he put it on the market,

23:56.469 --> 23:58.638
and he got rich off it.

23:58.738 --> 24:03.009
*

24:03.109 --> 24:06.045
- Milli Vanilli was delivered
by Frank Farian,

24:06.145 --> 24:08.915
and we were the distributor.

24:09.015 --> 24:13.853
We only saw the pictures of
the both guys and the song.

24:15.822 --> 24:17.323
Was nice-looking guys.

24:17.423 --> 24:20.259
Internationally, they could be
sold because they were colored

24:20.359 --> 24:22.795
and everything was--every--
it fits together.

24:22.895 --> 24:24.964
The product was great.
The music was great.

24:25.064 --> 24:27.567
The whole project is fantastic.

24:31.638 --> 24:32.805
- No, we didn't know it.

24:32.905 --> 24:34.741
I got tapes where--

24:34.841 --> 24:40.479
me, I was told that
it's Rob and Fab singing.

24:40.580 --> 24:45.752
- [speaking German]

24:45.852 --> 24:47.186
- One day,
we're at a friend's house

24:47.286 --> 24:49.956
watching "Formel Eins,"
this TV show...

24:50.056 --> 24:52.191
- [speaking German]

24:52.291 --> 24:54.994
- And then we see
Milli Vanilli.

24:55.094 --> 24:58.030
- Milli Vanilli,
"Girl You Know It's True."

24:58.130 --> 25:01.601
- Our name on television
on "Formel Eins."

25:01.701 --> 25:03.603
We used to dance
behind the stars

25:03.703 --> 25:05.237
who would come on this show,

25:05.337 --> 25:08.641
and suddenly,
we're in the charts.

25:08.741 --> 25:10.242
I mean, we went crazy.

25:10.342 --> 25:13.613
Running, like,
we even broke stuff.

25:13.713 --> 25:16.382
The song starts to blow up,

25:16.482 --> 25:18.551
and it happens so fast.

25:18.651 --> 25:20.386
Like, every week,
it was going up.

25:20.486 --> 25:21.988
Boom, boom, boom,
boom, boom, boom, boom,

25:22.088 --> 25:25.024
boom, boom, boom, boom,
boom, boom, pow!

25:25.124 --> 25:26.693
- And the song just takes off.

25:26.793 --> 25:28.227
It becomes a huge hit
in Germany.

25:32.498 --> 25:34.901
- Nobody knew
it was gonna be a hit.

25:35.001 --> 25:36.669
Not even Frank.

25:36.769 --> 25:38.871
But once he's seen
it was rising,

25:38.971 --> 25:41.273
then he started putting
more promotion into it.

25:41.373 --> 25:43.209
- Suddenly,
we were in "Bravo,"

25:43.309 --> 25:47.479
a youth magazine in Germany,
selling millions every week.

25:47.580 --> 25:50.016
People that were not
taking us seriously

25:50.116 --> 25:52.985
were suddenly like, "Hey."

25:53.085 --> 25:55.387
And now it's going through
Europe.

25:55.487 --> 25:59.091
So we travel up and down Europe
on television.

26:00.426 --> 26:01.828
We were nervous.

26:01.928 --> 26:03.395
"Can you drop your mic
a little bit?"

26:03.495 --> 26:05.231
No, I'm gonna keep it there.
[laughs]

26:05.331 --> 26:07.033
*

26:07.133 --> 26:10.903
But nervousness translated
into excitement.

26:11.003 --> 26:15.608
*

26:15.708 --> 26:18.410
A minute ago,
we didn't want to do this,

26:18.510 --> 26:21.113
but now, we want more.

26:21.213 --> 26:22.915
We were so pumped.

26:23.015 --> 26:25.818
You're in Italy,
you're in Spain,

26:25.918 --> 26:27.419
you're in Holland.

26:27.519 --> 26:30.056
- And then all of a sudden,
it hits the States.

26:30.890 --> 26:31.924
Bam.

26:32.024 --> 26:34.293
[loud explosion]

26:34.393 --> 26:37.329
[rock music]

26:37.429 --> 26:39.565
- * I'm in love with you, girl,
'cause you're on my mind *

26:39.666 --> 26:42.101
* You're the one I think about
most every time *

26:42.201 --> 26:44.637
* And when you pack a smile
in everything you do *

26:44.737 --> 26:46.973
* Don't you understand, girl,
this love is true *

26:47.073 --> 26:50.576
- They came in,
braids swinging...

26:50.677 --> 26:52.611
- Chest bumping...

26:52.712 --> 26:54.380
with tights on.

26:54.480 --> 26:58.050
- It was two Black dudes
with dreads coming into pop.

26:58.150 --> 27:01.053
That alone was
the shock factor.

27:01.153 --> 27:04.657
- * Girl, you know it's true

27:04.757 --> 27:07.727
* Ooh, ooh, ooh, I love you

27:07.827 --> 27:10.797
- The hair and the bandannas
and the shoulder pads.

27:10.897 --> 27:12.498
- * Yes, you know it's true

27:12.598 --> 27:14.433
- It was a totally
different style.

27:14.533 --> 27:17.036
both:
* Ooh, ooh, ooh, I love you

27:17.136 --> 27:18.805
- That's all we knew.
- They had it all.

27:18.905 --> 27:20.506
Like, their visuals were
on point.

27:20.606 --> 27:22.641
- I mean, they were
just eye candy.

27:22.742 --> 27:25.244
It was yummy, yummy, yummy.

27:25.344 --> 27:28.414
[upbeat funk music]

27:28.514 --> 27:30.516
- "Girl You Know It's True"
becomes the number two hit

27:30.616 --> 27:31.684
in the United States.

27:31.784 --> 27:33.452
- "Girl You Know It's True,"
number two.

27:33.552 --> 27:35.988
Oh, my God.

27:36.088 --> 27:40.492
- It became a top five hit in
23 countries around the world.

27:40.592 --> 27:43.863
That's Michael Jackson
level success.

27:43.963 --> 27:45.464
- Ah!

27:45.564 --> 27:46.632
[energizing music]

27:46.733 --> 27:48.467
- Great music, it just rises.

27:48.567 --> 27:52.371
When those special ones come,
they come.

27:52.471 --> 27:55.607
- As much as it wasn't
the right thing to do,

27:55.708 --> 27:58.210
the power of
"Girl You Know It's True"...

27:58.310 --> 27:59.979
* I'm so in love, girl

28:00.079 --> 28:01.080
Was pulling on us.

28:01.180 --> 28:02.681
* I'm so in love, girl

28:02.782 --> 28:04.150
*

28:04.250 --> 28:08.387
This energy, this hype...
- Do you want to party?

28:08.487 --> 28:11.690
- The love...
[loud cheering]

28:11.791 --> 28:15.027
So from that point on,

28:15.127 --> 28:18.164
we embraced the lie.

28:46.725 --> 28:48.594
- What's up?
- Running.

28:48.694 --> 28:50.429
- Yeah.

28:50.529 --> 28:53.232
Number one.
[music playing]

28:53.332 --> 28:54.366
- Every time we were
around people

28:54.466 --> 28:55.835
or, like, taking pictures...

28:55.935 --> 28:57.236
- OK.

28:58.237 --> 29:00.506
- We knew,
you know, you know.

29:00.606 --> 29:02.374
They don't know.
Do they know? I don't know.

29:05.644 --> 29:08.747
- But it was too difficult to
say no to this new life.

29:08.848 --> 29:12.351
[music playing]

29:12.451 --> 29:16.522
"Girl You Know It's True"
just unveiled the beast in us.

29:22.461 --> 29:23.562
- Yeah.

29:24.864 --> 29:29.401
*

29:29.501 --> 29:31.737
- We came from nothing
and now we were tasting

29:31.838 --> 29:33.840
this pop star life.

29:33.940 --> 29:36.408
To be adored, to be loved,

29:36.508 --> 29:39.711
that became very addictive.

30:02.734 --> 30:04.103
- I was nervous.

30:04.203 --> 30:10.242
Being caught was something that
was always, always very aware.

30:10.342 --> 30:12.845
- So, when will we have
your LP?

30:12.945 --> 30:15.447
- Gonna come out in two weeks.

30:15.547 --> 30:20.319
It's just like very pop
dance orientated music.

30:20.419 --> 30:22.621
Are you ready here?
[cheers]

30:24.723 --> 30:28.527
- For us, it was a surprise
that it developed immediately.

30:28.627 --> 30:30.829
It was worthwhile thinking
about what you can do.

30:30.930 --> 30:34.000
Do we need an album?
Yes, we need an album.

30:34.100 --> 30:37.169
Do we need a second single?
Yes, we need a second single.

30:37.269 --> 30:43.075
[soft dark music]

30:43.175 --> 30:45.377
- I get the call.

30:45.477 --> 30:46.946
"Frank needs to talk to you."

30:48.447 --> 30:51.083
So I goes up to the studio,

30:51.183 --> 30:54.420
Ingrid opened the door,
I go in.

30:54.520 --> 30:55.654
Sit in the kitchen and wait.

30:55.754 --> 30:58.557
*

30:58.657 --> 31:03.095
He came out--took his time,
fixed him a coffee--

31:03.195 --> 31:05.564
and then he said,

31:05.664 --> 31:08.734
"I told you,
keep your mouth shut."

31:08.834 --> 31:11.971
*

31:12.071 --> 31:16.208
He says to me, um,
"They found out in Munich,

31:16.308 --> 31:18.744
"from your promotion manager
or whoever,

31:18.844 --> 31:21.713
"that you're the voice.

31:21.813 --> 31:23.815
Don't want to
see you here anymore."

31:23.916 --> 31:25.684
We didn't talk anymore.

31:25.784 --> 31:29.421
That's it.

31:29.521 --> 31:34.360
I was kicked to the curb.

31:34.460 --> 31:37.229
[mysterious music]

31:37.329 --> 31:39.932
- One night,
Frank Farian called me up.

31:40.032 --> 31:42.901
He said, "John, I've got
a project I'm working on."

31:44.803 --> 31:49.575
"I had a rapper, Charles Shaw,
who tried the situation

31:49.675 --> 31:53.712
and he was not good so
can you come to the studio?"

31:53.812 --> 31:56.048
*

31:56.148 --> 31:58.350
So that's what I did.

31:58.450 --> 32:00.719
He said,
"You got 10,000 D-marks,"

32:00.819 --> 32:02.788
and I said, "Wow."

32:02.888 --> 32:05.891
He said, "You're gonna do
the whole album with me."

32:05.992 --> 32:09.561
- Frank said, "We're gonna be
doing more songs."

32:09.661 --> 32:11.797
- We always asked,
"Where is Rob and Fab?

32:11.897 --> 32:13.865
When are they gonna
start singing?"

32:13.966 --> 32:16.202
Frank said, "They're gonna
record in the evening

32:16.302 --> 32:17.769
when you guys are done."

32:36.522 --> 32:39.158
- I used to have to go through
the back door

32:39.258 --> 32:41.227
because Frank didn't want
nobody know

32:41.327 --> 32:43.529
I was the lead singer.

32:43.629 --> 32:45.931
- This is run like
a tight military operation.

32:46.032 --> 32:48.500
It's on a need-to-know basis.

32:48.600 --> 32:50.936
It was smoke and mirrors.

32:51.037 --> 32:55.474
David Copperfield
couldn't have done it better.

32:55.574 --> 32:58.777
- We like it hot, don't we?
[cheers and applause]

32:58.877 --> 33:01.480
You want to get down with
Milli Vanilli?

33:01.580 --> 33:04.150
They're coming.
It's a hit. Shake your booty.

33:04.250 --> 33:06.785
"Girl You Know It's True."

33:06.885 --> 33:09.821
[energetic music]

33:09.921 --> 33:17.029
*

33:17.629 --> 33:18.830
- One, mark.
- Mark.

33:18.930 --> 33:21.267
[boards click]

33:21.367 --> 33:23.602
- Make sure everyone's phone's
on silent.

33:23.702 --> 33:25.104
- That's a good idea.

33:25.204 --> 33:30.776
*

33:30.876 --> 33:34.413
- Clive is a--
is a gift-seeker.

33:34.513 --> 33:38.350
He is like the Yoda of talent.

33:38.450 --> 33:39.985
He knows.

33:40.086 --> 33:42.354
He just knows.

33:42.454 --> 33:45.757
- With Milli Vanilli,
Clive saw dollar signs.

33:45.857 --> 33:47.926
"Girl You Know It's True"
is big now.

33:48.026 --> 33:50.929
How can we cash in on
the immediate moment?

33:51.029 --> 33:54.200
- Well, we moved everything up
as fast as possible.

33:54.300 --> 33:57.035
- Clive would say every week
that we're missing,

33:57.136 --> 33:59.338
we're missing, like,
a million dollars.

33:59.438 --> 34:02.574
So we had to put
an album in motion.

34:02.674 --> 34:05.844
But the album that's out
in Europe, "All or Nothing,"

34:05.944 --> 34:09.915
was not strong enough
to release in America.

34:10.015 --> 34:12.484
- Clive called up
Diane Warren.

34:12.584 --> 34:14.320
- Diane Warren is one of
the biggest songwriters

34:14.420 --> 34:15.587
there are in the country.

34:15.687 --> 34:17.756
- I had written
"Blame It On The Rain"

34:17.856 --> 34:19.325
when I was scheduled
to see Clive,

34:19.425 --> 34:21.693
and he goes, I want you to
hear this new group I have.

34:21.793 --> 34:23.262
And he played me
"Girl You Know It's True."

34:23.362 --> 34:24.563
I'm like, "This is so crazy

34:24.663 --> 34:25.864
"'cause the song
I'm bringing you

34:25.964 --> 34:27.366
really sounds like
the follow-up to that."

34:27.466 --> 34:28.767
It's even the same rhythm.

34:28.867 --> 34:31.270
"Girl You Know It's True,"
"Blame It On The Rain."

34:31.370 --> 34:33.038
I played him the song
and he loved it.

34:33.139 --> 34:35.874
He sent it to Frank Farian
and they recorded it.

34:35.974 --> 34:38.510
*

34:38.610 --> 34:41.547
- Normally,
when you've given the producer

34:41.647 --> 34:44.383
some repertoire
for them to record,

34:44.483 --> 34:47.453
you want to be there
to make sure it gets done.

34:47.553 --> 34:49.521
In the case of Frank, though,

34:49.621 --> 34:52.291
he didn't want anyone
in the studio.

34:52.391 --> 34:55.093
[mysterious music]

34:55.194 --> 34:59.431
- It was very weird for us
to find the songs,

34:59.531 --> 35:01.032
send them to Frank,

35:01.133 --> 35:06.705
and then have them produce it
without any of our presence.

35:06.805 --> 35:11.143
But the speculation that
we were somehow aware of

35:11.243 --> 35:14.246
what was going on
behind the scenes in Germany

35:14.346 --> 35:17.749
is simply not the case.

35:17.849 --> 35:22.621
If an outside producer sends
in all the album credits,

35:22.721 --> 35:24.223
you have to take it on faith

35:24.323 --> 35:27.759
that represents what actually
happened in the studio.

35:27.859 --> 35:30.061
There was no reason
to think not.

35:35.267 --> 35:36.802
- Ah, there it is.

35:36.902 --> 35:40.038
So this is the European version
of the album "All or Nothing."

35:40.138 --> 35:43.275
You see Rob and Fab on
the cover, the first album.

35:43.375 --> 35:45.611
That's their, like,
running man logo.

35:45.711 --> 35:46.745
There they are on the back,

35:46.845 --> 35:49.681
shirtless, of course,
'cause why not?

35:49.781 --> 35:54.586
And let's see
who's credited on this album.

35:57.523 --> 36:00.592
