a band together.

40:37.869 --> 40:39.971
*

40:40.071 --> 40:41.840
- I was the band leader then.

40:41.940 --> 40:44.710
We had rehearsed,
we were flawless.

40:44.810 --> 40:47.278
Everybody was really
invested in this gig

40:47.378 --> 40:50.549
'cause it was
the new hottest shit, you know?

40:50.649 --> 40:52.718
After we had been approved,

40:52.818 --> 40:56.788
Rob and Fab disappeared.
They were gone.

40:56.888 --> 41:00.526
So we were just rehearsing
with no artist.

41:00.626 --> 41:04.896
And I start going, "These guys
must be really, really good.

41:04.996 --> 41:07.098
"They don't rehearse,
they don't fucking do nothing.

41:07.198 --> 41:10.736
They--
what the hell's going on?"

41:10.836 --> 41:12.370
We started asking
more questions.

41:12.470 --> 41:15.206
We got to realize, this musical
director at the time

41:15.306 --> 41:19.611
is programming this Oberheim.
There's where the vocals are.

41:19.711 --> 41:23.348
And then we understood,
"Oh, they're lip-syncing."

41:23.448 --> 41:26.051
So we said, "OK, we're in
a lip-sync band."

41:26.151 --> 41:27.519
[laughs]

41:27.619 --> 41:29.655
They said, "Don't say anything
about this to anybody else."

41:29.755 --> 41:30.856
"Fine."

41:30.956 --> 41:33.859
[hip-hop music]

41:33.959 --> 41:38.196
- The show would play
to packed arenas.

41:38.296 --> 41:43.334
Rob and Fab were two sexy
performers selling hits,

41:43.434 --> 41:46.538
and they did a really
bloody good job at it.

41:46.638 --> 41:51.309
[wild cheers and applause]

41:51.409 --> 41:54.379
