playing]

41:54.479 --> 41:58.950
*

41:59.050 --> 42:04.656
- [screams]

42:04.756 --> 42:11.096
- Yeah!

42:11.196 --> 42:14.800
* Girl, you know it's true

42:14.900 --> 42:20.939
* Ooh, ooh, ooh, I love you

42:21.039 --> 42:23.008
* Yes, you know it's true

42:23.108 --> 42:26.745
[wild cheers and applause]

42:26.845 --> 42:28.847
- The audience loved them.

42:28.947 --> 42:31.683
- Yeah!

42:31.783 --> 42:34.019
- It was very powerful.

42:34.119 --> 42:36.121
- * Girl, you know it's,
girl, you know it's *

42:36.221 --> 42:38.523
* Girl, you know it's true

42:38.624 --> 42:40.959
* Girl, you know it's,
yes, you know it's *

42:41.059 --> 42:44.562
* Girl, you know it's true

42:44.663 --> 42:48.433
- Performing is a drug.

42:48.533 --> 42:53.639
That euphoric feeling allowed
us to just forget everything.

42:53.739 --> 43:00.478
*

43:02.981 --> 43:06.451
[wild cheering]

43:06.551 --> 43:08.486
- Milli Vanilli,
the European duo,

43:08.586 --> 43:10.588
now one of the hottest
groups in America,

43:10.689 --> 43:13.792
made a special trip to the
Disney MGM Studios theme parks

43:13.892 --> 43:14.860
where we arranged
for them to have

43:14.960 --> 43:16.427
an exclusive interview session

43:16.527 --> 43:18.664
with some of
their most loyal fans.

43:18.764 --> 43:20.165
- Wherever you've performed,

43:20.265 --> 43:23.334
has anything really
embarrassing happened to you?

43:23.434 --> 43:24.636
- Yeah.

43:24.736 --> 43:27.005
[laughter]

43:27.105 --> 43:29.941
[tense music]

43:30.041 --> 43:34.179
*

43:34.279 --> 43:36.381
- It was super hot that day.

43:36.481 --> 43:40.752
"Downtown" Julie Brown
introduces us as usual.

43:47.759 --> 43:49.327
- I decided to take a break--

43:49.427 --> 43:52.463
the show had been going now
for a few months--

43:52.563 --> 43:55.400
and it was while
I was in my trailer

43:55.500 --> 44:00.105
I heard the crowd, like,
getting a little bit rowdy.

44:00.205 --> 44:02.173
[crowd shouting and booing]

44:02.273 --> 44:04.810
- The vocals that were
being cued from the emulator

44:04.910 --> 44:06.077
started repeating.

44:06.177 --> 44:07.545
* Girl, you know it's--

44:07.645 --> 44:09.981
* Girl, you know it's--
girl, you know it's-- *

44:10.081 --> 44:11.850
* Girl, you know it's--

44:11.950 --> 44:14.619
- It was like--
[imitating heartbeat]

44:14.720 --> 44:15.687
Shit!

44:15.787 --> 44:18.189
[crowd shouting and booing]

44:18.289 --> 44:22.160
- As I open my door,
I saw Rob go flying by.

44:22.260 --> 44:25.230
- Rob and Fab were gone,
and I'm onstage still with

44:25.330 --> 44:27.232
the guitar player and the
drummer going "What the fuck?

44:27.332 --> 44:29.701
Do we continue the song on
or what are we doing here?"

44:29.801 --> 44:31.336
[crowd booing]

44:31.436 --> 44:32.704
So, of course,
there was outrage.

44:32.804 --> 44:33.972
I was furious.

44:34.072 --> 44:36.674
"What the fuck, you know?
Find him!"

44:36.775 --> 44:39.811
- Rob was pissed.
He was like, "Fuck that!"

44:39.911 --> 44:42.080
He lost his cool.

44:42.180 --> 44:44.716
- Rob had gotten hold of me
to say,

44:44.816 --> 44:45.884
"I don't know what to do."

44:45.984 --> 44:47.618
You know, he was scared.

44:47.719 --> 44:49.921
*

44:50.021 --> 44:51.322
He kind of exploded.

44:51.422 --> 44:57.128
It was the moment where
it just burst open.

44:57.228 --> 44:58.897
And at that time,
we didn't know

44:58.997 --> 45:02.968
what pressure he was feeling
because we didn't know

45:03.068 --> 45:04.770
the load they were carrying.

45:04.870 --> 45:09.374
*

45:29.828 --> 45:33.264
[radio tuning]

45:33.364 --> 45:36.768
- * On the rain
