45:36.868 --> 45:37.869
- When Milli Vanilli blew up,

45:37.969 --> 45:39.370
I was a program director at

45:39.470 --> 45:44.275
WILD radio station, Boston.
1090 on the AM dial.

45:44.375 --> 45:49.080
The only Black station
within miles

45:49.180 --> 45:51.582
of Boston, Massachusetts.

45:51.682 --> 45:53.018
[hip-hop music]

45:53.118 --> 45:56.387
The guys came to our radio
station for our morning show.

45:56.487 --> 45:57.755
And I remember
them sitting there,

45:57.856 --> 45:59.357
and when I heard them talk
for the first time,

45:59.457 --> 46:01.860
I'm like,
"Oh, they sound very different

46:01.960 --> 46:04.095
than they do on the record."

46:04.195 --> 46:05.296
[laughs and claps]

46:05.396 --> 46:07.765
- Please welcome Milli Vanilli.

46:07.866 --> 46:10.869
[wild cheering]

46:10.969 --> 46:13.504
- Once they started doing
promotional dates,

46:13.604 --> 46:16.241
it became pretty clear
that something was strange.

46:16.341 --> 46:17.876
- Fab, how are you
finding Australia?

46:17.976 --> 46:19.310
You enjoying it?

46:22.013 --> 46:23.614
- Sydney?
[laughter]

46:23.714 --> 46:25.516
Syd-ney. Syd-ney.

46:26.151 --> 46:29.855
- Melbourne. Melbourne.
[laughter]

46:31.356 --> 46:35.060
- It just seemed that
they weren't comfortable

46:35.160 --> 46:37.295
communicating in English.

46:37.395 --> 46:40.031
- Who inspired you
the most, Rob?

46:40.131 --> 46:42.533
- Uh, diff--difficult.

46:42.633 --> 46:45.170
- You could tell
they were sweating bullets.

46:45.270 --> 46:46.304
