48:46.757 --> 48:48.659
[wild cheering]

49:02.407 --> 49:06.644
[wild cheering]

49:18.223 --> 49:21.692
[wild cheering]

49:24.529 --> 49:26.797
- I was a little bit
tired by it, yeah.

49:36.574 --> 49:40.211
- We drank more,
took more drugs,

49:40.311 --> 49:43.348
to be able to, like, numb out.

50:02.967 --> 50:05.436
- I think next time,
next time, maybe--

50:05.536 --> 50:07.004
should we ask them to sing
next time?

50:07.105 --> 50:09.740
[wild cheering]

50:17.848 --> 50:19.917
- Um...

50:20.017 --> 50:23.421
This, uh..

50:31.028 --> 50:33.964
[soft music]

51:26.417 --> 51:33.591
*

51:43.868 --> 51:47.272
- [shouts]

51:48.173 --> 51:50.308
- They got double platinum.
They got gold records.

51:50.408 --> 51:52.943
*

51:53.043 --> 51:55.346
Everybody else got
a gold record of my voice

51:55.446 --> 51:56.847
on their walls.

51:56.947 --> 51:58.483
*

51:58.583 --> 52:01.952
That's my voice!

52:02.052 --> 52:03.754
You end up drinking,

52:03.854 --> 52:07.325
you end up taking drugs
to not think about

52:07.425 --> 52:09.927
what's really happening
in reality.

52:10.027 --> 52:13.063
Then my manager that I had
at that time said,

52:13.164 --> 52:15.032
"Well, you know what?

52:15.132 --> 52:19.237
We're gonna do interviews.
You're gonna go live."

52:19.337 --> 52:20.905
I was singing before
Milli Vanilli

52:21.005 --> 52:23.140
